18/10/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul left for Berlin Sunday (17 October), telling reporters that Ankara is counting on Germany's support for receiving a date for starting EU accession negotiations, as well as for its EU bid in general. 
Gul will hold talks Monday with his German counterpart, Joschka Fischer, and other officials. 
He said he would raise concerns over some clauses in the European Commission's latest report on his country.
In other news Sunday, one Turkish soldier died and another was wounded in clashes with KONGRA-GEL terrorists. 
The fighting occurred in the eastern province of Tunceli. 
(NTV - 18/10/04; Turks.US, AFP - 17/10/04)
